==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entrap
<hw>En*trap"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Entrapped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Entrapping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>en-</ets>
+ <ets>trap</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>entraper</ets>.]</ety> <def>To catch in
a trap; to insnare; hence, to catch, as in a trap, by artifices; to
involve in difficulties or distresses; to catch or involve in
contradictions; <as>as, to be <ex>entrapped</ex> by the devices of evil
men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A golden mesh, to <qex>entrap</qex> the hearts of men.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To insnare; inveigle; tangle; decoy;
entangle.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entreat</ent>⟦br⟧
